problem_text: All rabbits are cute. Some turtles exist. An animal is either a rabbit or a squirrel. If something is skittish, then it is not still. All squirrels are skittish. Rock is still.
predicates:
Rabbit(x) ::: x is a rabbit.
Cute(x) ::: x is cute.
Turtle(x) ::: x is a turtle.
Exists(x) ::: x exists.
Animal(x) ::: x is an animal.
Squirrel(x) ::: x is a squirrel.
Skittish(x) ::: x is skittish.
Still(x) ::: x is still.
Is(x, y) ::: x is y.
Rock(x) ::: x is Rock.

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If something is a rabbit, then it is not skittish.
tests.conclusions: ¬∃x (Rabbit(x) → Skittish(x)) ::: If something is a rabbit, then it is not skittish. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If something is a squirrel, then it is cute.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If something is a rabbit, then it is cute and it is an animal.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If something is a squirrel, then it is not still.
tests.conclusions: ∀x (Squirrel(x) → ¬Still(x)) ::: If something is a squirrel, then it is not still. TRUE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If something is a rabbit, then it is cute and it is not skittish.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Rock is not an animal.
tests.conclusions: ¬Animal(rock) ::: Rock is not an animal. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? Rock is a rabbit or a squirrel.
tests.conclusions: Rock(rock) ∧ (Rabbit(rock) ∨ Squirrel(rock)) ::: Rock is a rabbit or a squirrel. FALSE

tests.questions: Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If something is a squirrel, then it is cute.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If something is a rabbit, then it is not a squirrel.
Based on the above information, is the following statement true or false? If something is an animal and not a rabbit, then it is a squirrel.
